<%# Phase 27 §01c-v2 — Outer Custom collections shelf (nested).
    Supersedes the v1 flat-tile design. The outer shelf is a single
    `<section data-shelf="outer-collections">` carrying an `<h2>`
    heading; inside it iterates one sub-shelf per collection that
    owns at least one game (alphabetical, case-insensitive). Each
    sub-shelf is a row with a leading composite cover tile followed
    by `Games::CoverComponent` game tiles at `:shelf` variant.

    Empty buckets are hidden — when no collection owns any game, the
    entire `<section>` is suppressed (no muted placeholder, no `<h2>`).
    This intentionally reverses 01c-v1 per 01c-v2 locked decision #7.

    Locals:
      collections  ActiveRecord::Relation of Collection rows, pre-
                   filtered by the caller to only include collections
                   that own at least one game and pre-ordered
                   alphabetical case-insensitive.
%>
<%
  collections = local_assigns.fetch(:collections)
%>
<% if collections.any? %>
  <section class="shelf shelf--collections outer-shelf" data-shelf="outer-collections" style="margin-top: 16px;">
    <div class="dot-list" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
      <h2 style="margin: 0;">custom collections</h2>
    </div>

    <% collections.each do |collection| %>
      <%= render "games/collection_sub_shelf_row", collection: collection %>
    <% end %>
  </section>
<% end %>
